heir stories and voices to the fore. Ultimately, Villalón proposes an active policy advocacy agenda and suggests possible changes to gender violence-based immigration laws, revealing the complexities of the lives of Latina immigrants as they confront issues of citizenship, gender violence, and social inequalities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLatin AmericansxViolence againstzUnited States. 0aLatin AmericanszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aWomen immigrantsxViolence againstzUnited States. 0aWomen immigrantszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Hispanic American Studies.2bisacsh  aCaught.  aLatina.  aRoberta.  aVillalon.  aabuse.  abeen.  abetween.  abureaucratic.  acitizenship.  acomplexities.  acomplications.  adelivery.  adomestic.  aeven.  aexplores.  afree.  agroup.  aimmigrant.  aimmigrants.  aimmigration.  ainequality.  ainnovative.  aintersection.  alegal.  amany.  amostly.  anonprofit.  aoffers.  aparticularly.  apartners.  aperpetuated.  aservices.  ashows.  astudy.  asurvivors.  asystem.  athat.  athrough.  aundocumented.  avictims.  aviolence.  aviolent.  avital.  avolunteered.  avulnerable.  awell-intentioned.  awomen.  ayears.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081478823340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814788233.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814788424423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814788424/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_